description:
&lt;p&gt;If you’re ready to take your nursing career to the next level, Ward B4 has a Deputy Sister/Charge Nurse Post available. This new role provides real career progression for ambitious Band 5 nurses, and existing Band 6 nurses looking for their next challenge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you want to work and develop in a supportive working environment at a hospital that 90 per cent of its staff would recommend to their friends and family, and rated ‘good’ by its regulator, contact us to find out more.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Personalised training and development plans, including access to our university-recognised Leading Safe and Effective Quality Patient Care programme, will see you rapidly develop your skills and experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If your ethos is one of continuous improvement, and are driven to provide compassionate, open, respectful, accountable and safe care every day, we want to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are welcomed from both current Poole Hospital staff and external applicants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If this job requires you to have a DBS check to enable you to properly fulfil the requirements of the job, on appointment you will be required to repay the cost of obtaining a DBS check and this amount will be reclaimed from your salary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 10/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Provisional interview date: week commencing 23/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Zoe Bagg, Ward Sister&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;zoe.bagg@uhd.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details or to arrange an informal visit contact us on 0300 019 8567 or 0300 019 2413.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look forward to hearing from you.&lt;/p&gt;
